main_body:
Article 2(1) of Regulation (EC) No 1554/2001 is replaced by the following: "1. On application to the competent French authorities, for the 2002/03 to 2005/06 marketing years producers of the sugar referred to in Article 1 and delivered to European ports in the Community shall be granted aid made up of the following components:
(a) a flat-rate amount per tonne of sugar expressed as white sugar to cover the transport costs from the ex-factory stage to the fob port stage, fixed at:
- EUR 17 per tonne for RĂŠunion and Martinique,
- EUR 24 per tonne for Guadeloupe;
(b) a uniform flat-rate amount to cover the sea transport costs from the fob port in overseas department stage to the cif European ports in the Community stage and the related insurance costs;
(c) a flat-rate amount per 100 kilograms of raw sugar expressed as white sugar held in storage by producers at the end of each month, fixed at EUR 0,45 for Guadeloupe and at EUR 0,35 for RĂŠunion."
